  "writeup": "The Buffalo Bills officially unveiled their new $2.1 billion Highmark Stadium in Orchard Park with a ribbon-cutting ceremony, drawing widespread praise for its impressive features and design. The celebration was tempered by an emotional revelation from Bills legend Jim Kelly, who disclosed he suffered a stroke this past spring but assured fans he is feeling 'really good' now. On the roster front, the Kyle Pitts contract extension is drawing attention for its potential impact on tight end Dalton Kincaid's future deal negotiations, while debates over the RB2 role and players on the roster bubble continue to percolate heading into the 2026 season. New offensive coordinator Joe Brady has also been drawing rave reviews from players for reshaping the team's culture during the offseason program.",
